1
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:04,321
(GLASS SPEAKING PAWNEE)

2
00:01:04,446 --> 00:01:07,324
It's okay, son...

3
00:01:08,617 --> 00:01:13,497
I know you want this to be over.

4
00:01:20,004 --> 00:01:22,131
I'm right here.

5
00:01:26,510 --> 00:01:29,179
I will be right here...

6
00:01:36,687 --> 00:01:39,106
But, you don't give up.

7
00:01:42,067 --> 00:01:45,029
You hear me?

8
00:01:46,864 --> 00:01:51,910
As long as you can still
grab a breath, you fight.

9
00:01:53,537 --> 00:01:56,957
You breathe... keep breathing.

10
00:03:42,396 --> 00:03:43,439
(GLASS CLICKS TONGUE)

11
00:03:43,522 --> 00:03:44,857
GLASS: Hawk.

12
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,592
(GUNS COCKING)
(GLASS CLICKS TONGUE)

13
00:04:11,717 --> 00:04:13,218
(GLASS SPEAKING PAWNEE)

14
00:04:31,069 --> 00:04:33,071
Ah, shit.

15
00:04:34,907 --> 00:04:37,576
Goddamn sumbitches.

16
00:04:39,745 --> 00:04:42,414
The sumbitch
got shit for brains.

17
00:04:42,539 --> 00:04:44,041
(GRUMBLING)

18
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,921
You seen Coulter?

19
00:04:49,087 --> 00:04:50,088
TRAPPER: Nope.

20
00:04:53,050 --> 00:04:54,384
Listen up!

21
00:04:54,593 --> 00:04:56,053
When them plews is cleaned,

22
00:04:56,136 --> 00:04:58,263
I want you to hoop 'em up
real tight.

23
00:04:58,597 --> 00:05:02,559
Remember, we're not doing
no 15-pelt bales!

24
00:05:02,559 --> 00:05:03,519
We're going
30-pelt bales!

25
00:05:03,602 --> 00:05:04,603
HENRY: Fitzgerald!

26
00:05:05,562 --> 00:05:06,647
Cap'n.

27
00:05:06,730 --> 00:05:09,650
Where are we with the haul?
What are you thinking?

28
00:05:10,943 --> 00:05:13,862
I'm thinking, whatever it is
they're hunting out there...

29
00:05:13,946 --> 00:05:15,864
...I' hope it don't need
another shot.

30
00:05:15,948 --> 00:05:18,075
Make sure we're ready
to head out by dawn.

31
00:05:18,158 --> 00:05:19,201
Been done
by this morning.

32
00:05:19,284 --> 00:05:20,744
I'd have liked
to be out by how,

33
00:05:20,828 --> 00:05:22,871
but the men
are too tired.

34
00:05:22,955 --> 00:05:24,331
We're only a few days
from the fort.

35
00:05:24,414 --> 00:05:25,457
We're trapped out.

36
00:05:25,541 --> 00:05:28,919
All we have to worry about
is fresh meat for the boys.

37
00:05:29,253 --> 00:05:31,839
Well, you, uh,
seen Coulter?

38
00:05:31,922 --> 00:05:33,590
(JIM PANTING)

39
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:37,636
JIM: Hey, we took down
an elk. A big one.

40
00:05:38,637 --> 00:05:40,430
We need help
to haul the meat back.

41
00:05:40,597 --> 00:05:42,057
Let me know
when it's on the spit.

42
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:43,392
I'll help you
with it then.

43
00:05:43,475 --> 00:05:45,227
Come on, I need your help.

44
00:05:45,310 --> 00:05:47,646
We needed help when we were
loading them bales.

45
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:50,649
I been eating this damn
beaver meat so long...

46
00:05:50,983 --> 00:05:52,943
...I'm starting to
miss my wife's cooking.

47
00:05:53,277 --> 00:05:54,695
I'm starting
to miss your wife.

48
00:05:54,778 --> 00:05:55,821
Shut up.

49
00:05:56,154 --> 00:05:57,322
COULTER: Help!

50
00:05:58,156 --> 00:05:59,491
Help.

51
00:05:59,992 --> 00:06:01,326
TRAPPER 1: Is that Coulter?
(MEN CLAMORING)

52
00:06:01,660 --> 00:06:03,787
You go get the Captain.

53
00:06:03,954 --> 00:06:05,289
STUBBY BILL: Jesus Christ.

54
00:06:08,458 --> 00:06:10,168
TRAPPER 2: Anybody see them?

55
00:06:10,502 --> 00:06:11,795
TRAPPER 3: Stay quiet.

56
00:06:11,962 --> 00:06:13,171
TRAPPER 4: Watch the ridge.

57
00:06:13,297 --> 00:06:14,965
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

58
00:06:15,966 --> 00:06:16,967
(GROANS)

59
00:06:22,639 --> 00:06:23,974
(HAWK SPEAKING PAWNEE)

60
00:06:24,099 --> 00:06:26,226
What was that?

61
00:06:32,107 --> 00:06:33,025
Pa?

62
00:06:33,358 --> 00:06:34,610
Let's go.

63
00:06:45,537 --> 00:06:47,039
(MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

64
00:06:48,665 --> 00:06:49,958
(MAN SHUSHING)

65
00:06:50,042 --> 00:06:51,835
(HORSES WHINNYING)
(ARIKARA WARRIORS WHOOPING)

66
00:06:56,048 --> 00:06:57,716
They got Thomas.

67
00:07:20,906 --> 00:07:23,575
I can't see 'em.
I can't see 'em.

68
00:07:28,580 --> 00:07:30,082
HENRY: Get down!

69
00:07:31,583 --> 00:07:34,086
We're surrounded!
They're everywhere!

70
00:07:34,378 --> 00:07:36,088
HENRY: Stay here! Stay here!

71
00:07:36,213 --> 00:07:37,172
(PAUL GROANING)

72
00:07:37,255 --> 00:07:38,590
Paul, no!

73
00:07:38,882 --> 00:07:40,425
(PAUL SCREAMING)

74
00:07:47,391 --> 00:07:49,393
They want us out in the open.

75
00:07:50,268 --> 00:07:52,771
Nobody move!
Stay where you are!

76
00:07:53,105 --> 00:07:54,815
They want the pelts.

77
00:07:54,898 --> 00:07:56,566
We got to get
on that boat right now

78
00:07:56,650 --> 00:07:58,110
or we'll lose it all.

79
00:08:03,407 --> 00:08:05,242
(ARIKARA WARRIORS WHOOPING)

80
00:08:07,577 --> 00:08:09,246
(SHOUTING IN PAWNEE)

81
00:08:15,794 --> 00:08:19,297
Get to the boat!
To the boat, son! Move!

82
00:08:19,923 --> 00:08:21,258
Move, move!

83
00:08:21,675 --> 00:08:23,093
(BOTH GRUNTING)

84
00:08:24,302 --> 00:08:28,140
Leave the furs!
Leave the furs! To the boat!

85
00:08:28,765 --> 00:08:29,933
(YELLING)

86
00:08:31,309 --> 00:08:32,769
(BOTH GRUNTING)

87
00:08:47,034 --> 00:08:48,452
(ARIKARA WARRIOR 1 GROANING)

88
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:55,459
Hawk!

89
00:09:01,465 --> 00:09:02,966
Hawk!

90
00:09:03,341 --> 00:09:04,968
Hawk!

91
00:09:15,062 --> 00:09:16,730
(ARIKARA WARRIOR 2 WHOOPING)

92
00:09:20,317 --> 00:09:21,651
(SHOUTING IN ARIKARA)

93
00:09:24,071 --> 00:09:25,405
(GROANING)

94
00:09:33,205 --> 00:09:36,541
Grab some pelts!
Come on, grab the pelts!

95
00:09:41,254 --> 00:09:42,923
(BOTH GRUNTING)

96
00:09:55,894 --> 00:09:59,564
Grab the pelts!
Grab the pelts!

97
00:10:15,705 --> 00:10:17,415
DAVE: Give this
to my little girl.

98
00:10:17,749 --> 00:10:19,751
You're coming with us.
I'll get help.

99
00:10:26,925 --> 00:10:29,594
GLASS: Leave the furs!
Leave the pelts!

100
00:10:30,428 --> 00:10:31,555
Willman!

101
00:10:32,597 --> 00:10:33,849
Lean on me.
Just keep going.

102
00:10:33,932 --> 00:10:35,100
(GROANS)

103
00:10:38,603 --> 00:10:40,605
Get to the boat!

104
00:10:44,067 --> 00:10:45,944
(ARIKARA WARRIORS WHOOPING)

105
00:10:47,988 --> 00:10:49,406
(YELLING)

106
00:11:02,586 --> 00:11:04,087
Fucking savage!

107
00:11:05,422 --> 00:11:07,632
Get on the fucking boat!

108
00:11:14,639 --> 00:11:15,932
(GROANING)

109
00:11:17,267 --> 00:11:18,602
Help!

110
00:11:30,655 --> 00:11:32,991
HENRY: Cut the rope!
Cut the rope!

111
00:11:33,325 --> 00:11:34,826
Wait for Amos!

112
00:11:34,993 --> 00:11:36,494
No! We go now!

113
00:11:36,828 --> 00:11:38,663
Fire the cannon!

114
00:11:49,007 --> 00:11:51,509
AMOS: Don't leave! Wait!

115
00:12:01,478 --> 00:12:03,355
(ARIKARA ELDER CHANTING)

116
00:12:37,347 --> 00:12:39,766
My daughter, Powaqa, is not here.

117
00:12:40,642 --> 00:12:42,435
Collect all the pelts we can carry.

118
00:12:43,186 --> 00:12:50,151
We'll trade pelts with the French
for horses and keep searching for her.

119
00:12:53,071 --> 00:12:54,906
HENRY:
- -and dust becomes flour...

120
00:12:55,532 --> 00:12:57,200
...and when the morning
is clear...

121
00:12:57,367 --> 00:13:01,579
...this child of God will meet
Jesus Christ himself. Amen.

122
00:13:09,587 --> 00:13:11,464
(MURPHY BREATHING SHAKILY)

123
00:13:16,594 --> 00:13:17,762
HENRY: You ready?

124
00:13:19,764 --> 00:13:21,099
Hold still.

125
00:13:21,308 --> 00:13:22,934
(MURPHY SCREAMING)

126
00:13:26,438 --> 00:13:27,939
ANDERSON:
Where did you learn that?

127
00:13:28,732 --> 00:13:31,109
My father was a doctor.
Bridger!

128
00:13:31,443 --> 00:13:32,694
FITZGERALD: Captain,
we got a swarm of

129
00:13:32,777 --> 00:13:35,613
tree niggers out here
waiting to finish the job.

130
00:13:38,950 --> 00:13:41,411
Tell me you got
some kind of plan.

131
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:47,625
Glass?

132
00:13:48,793 --> 00:13:50,795
Missouri's no good.

133
00:13:51,296 --> 00:13:53,590
Not while the Ree's
running it.

134
00:13:53,965 --> 00:13:55,592
We got to
get off this boat.

135
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,802
Oh, you want to
get off the boat?

136
00:13:59,262 --> 00:14:01,139
Then what do we do, huh?

137
00:14:01,473 --> 00:14:03,767
Take our furs
and sit out there
amongst the Ree

138
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:05,477
like a bunch of ducks?

139
00:14:05,810 --> 00:14:08,980
Only safe thing to do
is track a new course
back up on land.

140
00:14:09,147 --> 00:14:10,482
That'll add weeks
to the trip.

141
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:12,692
Better than floating
where they can get eyes on us.

142
00:14:12,984 --> 00:14:15,320
They got eyes on you
right now, son.

143
00:14:16,654 --> 00:14:19,491
What I'm saying is
we stay on the boat.

144
00:14:19,824 --> 00:14:21,993
Chart a course
toward the fort

145
00:14:22,118 --> 00:14:23,495
and take our chances
on the water.

146
00:14:23,578 --> 00:14:26,539
Glass knows
this territory best.

147
00:14:26,623 --> 00:14:28,166
It's his job
to get us home safe.

148
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:29,417
Get us home safe?
Yeah.

149
00:14:29,501 --> 00:14:31,920
FITZGERALD: Need I remind you
we already lost 32 men?

150
00:14:32,003 --> 00:14:34,214
It's 33 now.
They were my men, Fitzgerald.

151
00:14:34,297 --> 00:14:36,132
I know how many I lost.

152
00:14:37,008 --> 00:14:39,636
We do like Glass says.
That's the end of it.

153
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:54,567
GLASS: We have to
set the boat loose.

154
00:14:54,651 --> 00:14:57,153
If the Ree are tracking us,
they'll find it downriver.

155
00:14:57,487 --> 00:14:59,322
Best course is to
hike inland to the Grand

156
00:14:59,406 --> 00:15:01,074
and follow it
to Fort Kiowa.

157
00:15:01,157 --> 00:15:03,034
ANDERSON: On foot?

158
00:15:03,118 --> 00:15:04,327
It'll be winter
before we get there.

159
00:15:04,411 --> 00:15:06,037
Yeah, unless
we come across a post,

160
00:15:06,121 --> 00:15:07,247
trade for some horses.

161
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:09,165
Ain't no posts
that far over!

162
00:15:09,499 --> 00:15:12,585
Captain, losing this boat
is a goddamn mistake.

163
00:15:12,919 --> 00:15:15,004
The Ree
ain't that stupid.

164
00:15:15,130 --> 00:15:17,590
We keep it, we can lay it up
around Arrow's Peak.

165
00:15:17,674 --> 00:15:19,759
Quit acting like you know
what you're talking about.

166
00:15:19,843 --> 00:15:21,344
Ain't nobody
talking to you.

167
00:15:21,594 --> 00:15:23,012
Who'd listen
to you anyway?

168
00:15:23,138 --> 00:15:26,433
Can't find your way
out of your breeches
to take a shit.

169
00:15:26,516 --> 00:15:29,853
All I'm saying is
Camp Rhulen
is just up the way.

170
00:15:30,186 --> 00:15:31,938
We can hole up there.

171
00:15:32,355 --> 00:15:33,857
We walk.

172
00:15:34,524 --> 00:15:36,526
Yeah, I'm sure we will.

173
00:15:37,569 --> 00:15:39,320
Wish my dad
was a doctor.

174
00:15:39,404 --> 00:15:41,865
Then he could've bought me
a captain's job.

175
00:15:41,948 --> 00:15:43,283
What do we do, eh?

176
00:15:43,366 --> 00:15:46,536
Pray these pelts ain't rotten
if we ever get back here?

177
00:15:46,870 --> 00:15:48,288
HENRY: Make sure
to mark this place.

178
00:15:48,371 --> 00:15:50,874
We're leaving a fortune
under these rocks.

179
00:15:53,042 --> 00:15:54,461
Glass, chart a course.

180
00:15:54,544 --> 00:15:56,963
Tightest you can that
gets us around the Ree.

181
00:15:58,715 --> 00:16:00,383
FITZGERALD: This ain't right.

182
00:16:01,468 --> 00:16:04,387
We all know these furs

183
00:16:04,471 --> 00:16:06,473
ain't gonna be here
by the time we come back.

184
00:16:06,556 --> 00:16:10,143
There's no way
we can haul them
all the way to the fort.

185
00:16:10,226 --> 00:16:12,145
Arikara are
all through the territory.

186
00:16:12,228 --> 00:16:13,480
We'll want
our hands free.

187
00:16:13,563 --> 00:16:15,482
We're gonna
lose those pelts.

188
00:16:15,565 --> 00:16:17,066
You rather keep the pelts
or your life?

189
00:16:17,192 --> 00:16:18,401
Life?

190
00:16:18,651 --> 00:16:21,404
What life you talking about?
I ain't got no life.

191
00:16:21,654 --> 00:16:23,448
I just got living
and the only way I get that

192
00:16:23,531 --> 00:16:25,325
is through these pelts.

193
00:16:26,743 --> 00:16:27,994
Fuck!

194
00:16:30,246 --> 00:16:33,333
Ain't no way I'm going home
after six months

195
00:16:33,416 --> 00:16:35,251
working my ass off
like a mule...

196
00:16:35,668 --> 00:16:39,005
...risking my neck,
men dying, and for what?

197
00:16:39,088 --> 00:16:40,590
Damn near lost everything.

198
00:16:40,673 --> 00:16:42,926
Job's been fucked
from the start!

199
00:16:43,927 --> 00:16:45,929
There's the one
been fucking us.

200
00:16:46,429 --> 00:16:49,599
You wonder how the Ree
got the dead drop on us...

201
00:16:49,849 --> 00:16:50,975
...when Mr. Glass
was supposed

202
00:16:51,059 --> 00:16:52,977
to look out
for that very thing?

203
00:16:53,269 --> 00:16:55,355
All them
Pawnee buddies of his.

204
00:16:55,438 --> 00:16:58,274
Pawnee's as much against
the Ree as the rest of us.

205
00:16:58,358 --> 00:16:59,442
Yeah?

206
00:16:59,943 --> 00:17:03,613
Well, what about
his little half-breed son?

207
00:17:04,113 --> 00:17:06,449
What kind of savage
you think his mama was?

208
00:17:06,533 --> 00:17:08,368
Oh, lay off the boy, Fitz.

209
00:17:09,035 --> 00:17:10,787
All I'm saying is...

210
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:13,790
...a savage...is savage.

211
00:17:21,548 --> 00:17:23,216
Hey, Glass...

212
00:17:24,467 --> 00:17:25,718
...Is it true
what they say

213
00:17:25,802 --> 00:17:27,220
about you shooting
a lieutenant

214
00:17:27,303 --> 00:17:29,472
while living
with them savages?

215
00:17:33,142 --> 00:17:36,062
Twenty-one dead soldiers
and 40 dead feathernecks.

216
00:17:36,145 --> 00:17:38,314
But you and your boy
the only ones
to walk out alive.

217
00:17:38,439 --> 00:17:40,525
Kind of a miracle.

218
00:17:40,608 --> 00:17:41,985
HENRY: Shut up, Fitzgerald.

219
00:17:43,903 --> 00:17:45,154
FITZGERALD:
Is that what you did?

220
00:17:45,238 --> 00:17:47,657
Shot one of your own
to save this little dog here?

221
00:17:47,991 --> 00:17:49,284
Shut up!

222
00:17:49,492 --> 00:17:52,745
Why? Was he playing with
this little boy's mama, huh?

223
00:17:52,829 --> 00:17:54,497
Did he kill her?

224
00:17:55,164 --> 00:17:56,583
Hey, you can quit
polishing that rifle

225
00:17:56,666 --> 00:17:58,167
when I'm talking to you.

226
00:17:58,501 --> 00:17:59,919
I'm working on it.

227
00:18:00,003 --> 00:18:02,505
You can work on it
when I'm done
talking to you.

228
00:18:02,839 --> 00:18:03,923
Look at me.

229
00:18:04,007 --> 00:18:05,341
HENRY: That's enough!

230
00:18:06,509 --> 00:18:08,761
You're forgetting
your place, boy.

231
00:18:10,096 --> 00:18:12,098
As far as I can tell,
my place is here

232
00:18:12,181 --> 00:18:14,434
on the smart end
of this rifle.

233
00:18:14,517 --> 00:18:16,686
HENRY:
You move along, Fitzgerald.

234
00:18:18,354 --> 00:18:19,772
That's an order!

235
00:18:19,856 --> 00:18:20,898
Listen!

236
00:18:20,982 --> 00:18:22,775
There's only a couple hours
of light left.

237
00:18:22,859 --> 00:18:25,028
We got to stash these pelts
and get rid of the boat.

238
00:18:25,111 --> 00:18:26,362
Let's go!
(ALL AGREEING)

239
00:18:27,488 --> 00:18:28,531
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

240
00:18:28,781 --> 00:18:30,992
I told you to be invisible, son.

241
00:18:30,992 --> 00:18:32,327
At least he....

242
00:18:32,327 --> 00:18:36,331
- -If you want to survive,
keep your mouth shut.

243
00:18:36,331 --> 00:18:40,585
- At least he heard me...
- They don't hear your voice!

244
00:18:40,585 --> 00:18:43,046
They just see the color of your face.

245
00:18:43,046 --> 00:18:45,715
You understand?

246
00:18:45,715 --> 00:18:46,841
Yes.

247
00:18:51,638 --> 00:18:54,098
You have to listen to me, son.

248
00:18:54,098 --> 00:18:56,434
You have to listen.

249
00:19:01,481 --> 00:19:02,690
(GLASS GRUNTS)

250
00:19:08,488 --> 00:19:09,989
HENRY: Beckett!

251
00:19:11,157 --> 00:19:12,158
Weston!

252
00:19:12,325 --> 00:19:14,243
JONES: Why are
they not jumping?

253
00:19:14,911 --> 00:19:17,246
STUBBY BILL: It looks
like they changed their minds.

254
00:19:23,252 --> 00:19:25,254
FITZGERALD: Smart sumbitches.

255
00:19:25,922 --> 00:19:27,256
Smart.

256
00:19:28,216 --> 00:19:29,592
(GRUNTS)

257
00:19:33,596 --> 00:19:35,932
I ought to be
on that boat.

258
00:19:39,435 --> 00:19:41,437
They did the right thing.

259
00:19:46,317 --> 00:19:47,902
(MEN LAUGHING)

260
00:19:57,036 --> 00:19:58,121
(BOTH SPEAKING PAWNEE)

261
00:19:58,287 --> 00:19:59,747
It's time to move.

262
00:20:00,456 --> 00:20:01,958
Get up.

263
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,127
We're headed out.

264
00:20:06,963 --> 00:20:08,548
I'm coming.

265
00:20:11,384 --> 00:20:13,428
It's better you lay down.

266
00:20:15,346 --> 00:20:19,517
When the rest of the men are ready
you send them to me.

267
00:20:19,517 --> 00:20:21,477
I'm going west.

268
00:20:35,908 --> 00:20:41,789
You are my son.

269
00:20:49,964 --> 00:20:51,424
(WARRIOR 1 SPEAKING ARIKARA)

270
00:20:51,716 --> 00:20:53,092
There are only two here.

271
00:20:53,176 --> 00:20:54,260
(ELK DOG SPEAKING ARIKARA)

272
00:20:54,343 --> 00:20:57,180
Powagqga is not here.

273
00:20:57,263 --> 00:20:58,347
(WARRIOR 1 SPEAKING ARIKARA)

274
00:20:58,598 --> 00:21:01,058
The others probably took her.

275
00:21:01,058 --> 00:21:02,894
They went north.

276
00:21:03,019 --> 00:21:04,187
(ELK DOG SPEAKING ARIKARA)

277
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:08,357
We'll pick up their tracks on the mountain.

278
00:21:10,860 --> 00:21:12,445
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

279
00:21:16,491 --> 00:21:18,034
HENRY: Was it
the right decision?

280
00:21:18,159 --> 00:21:19,494
Leaving the boat?

281
00:21:20,495 --> 00:21:23,998
The Ree own that river.
They would've flanked us.

282
00:21:24,665 --> 00:21:27,043
We stay east of the Grand
through the mountains,

283
00:21:27,126 --> 00:21:28,753
we cut a week off our trip.

284
00:21:28,836 --> 00:21:31,881
Lands are bone dry up there.
Nothing for the Ree to hunt.

285
00:21:32,882 --> 00:21:34,342
HENRY: Except us.

286
00:21:34,675 --> 00:21:36,219
GLASS: Except us.

287
00:21:43,017 --> 00:21:45,019
Is it true
what Fitzgerald said?

288
00:21:46,521 --> 00:21:49,190
Is that why you
came out here to
the edge of the world?

289
00:21:52,026 --> 00:21:53,152
Glass?

290
00:21:53,236 --> 00:21:55,071
I do like the quiet.

291
00:21:57,198 --> 00:21:58,533
Your boy...

292
00:21:58,866 --> 00:22:00,535
...he's seen a lot.

293
00:22:01,202 --> 00:22:04,038
He got a mother
you need to get him back to?

294
00:22:08,793 --> 00:22:10,086
(FITZGERALD BREATHING HEAVILY)

295
00:22:10,169 --> 00:22:11,587
(CUTTING HAIR)

296
00:23:34,837 --> 00:23:36,088
(RUSTLING)

297
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:48,184
(COCKS GUN)

298
00:23:59,111 --> 00:24:00,613
(BEAR BELLOWING)

299
00:24:15,711 --> 00:24:17,380
(BEAR SNORTING)

300
00:24:20,967 --> 00:24:22,051
(GLASS YELLS)

301
00:24:22,385 --> 00:24:24,220
(GROANING)

302
00:24:42,905 --> 00:24:44,240
(SCREAMING)

303
00:25:07,054 --> 00:25:08,931
(BELLOWING)

304
00:25:16,689 --> 00:25:18,190
(GROANING)

305
00:25:39,962 --> 00:25:41,797
(GLASS PANTING)

306
00:25:50,598 --> 00:25:52,266
(STRAINING)

307
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:12,828
(FLIES BUZZING)

308
00:26:13,329 --> 00:26:14,497
(GRUNTS)

309
00:26:34,809 --> 00:26:36,852
(PANTING)

310
00:27:06,382 --> 00:27:07,842
(GRUNTING)

311
00:27:08,717 --> 00:27:10,803
(CHOKING)

312
00:27:15,057 --> 00:27:16,725
(SCREAMING)

313
00:28:30,132 --> 00:28:31,592
(BELLOWS)

314
00:28:32,551 --> 00:28:34,220
(GRUNTING)

315
00:28:49,902 --> 00:28:51,320
(CUB BELLOWING)

316
00:29:02,498 --> 00:29:03,582
(HAWK YELLING)

317
00:29:03,666 --> 00:29:05,751
JIM: Mr. Glass!

318
00:29:06,335 --> 00:29:07,920
There are cubs here!

319
00:29:11,507 --> 00:29:13,175
We got cubs here!

320
00:29:17,137 --> 00:29:18,806
Christ Almighty.

321
00:29:23,143 --> 00:29:24,645
He's down here!

322
00:29:26,772 --> 00:29:28,482
ANDERSON: Keep your eyes open.
There's bears around.

323
00:29:28,649 --> 00:29:30,526
JIM: I need your help now!

324
00:29:33,862 --> 00:29:35,281
HENRY: Oh, my God.

325
00:29:35,698 --> 00:29:37,032
(GLASS WHEEZING)

326
00:29:38,367 --> 00:29:40,244
Get me rags now!

327
00:29:40,327 --> 00:29:42,997
Give me rags
before he bleeds out. Rags.

328
00:29:43,831 --> 00:29:46,834
Prepare the kit. Bridger!
You hold that.

329
00:29:47,042 --> 00:29:48,460
(GRUNTING)

330
00:29:48,544 --> 00:29:50,296
Easy. Oh, my God.

331
00:29:50,379 --> 00:29:51,630
ANDERSON: Got to give him
credit for taking that grizz

332
00:29:51,714 --> 00:29:52,965
down with him.

333
00:29:53,048 --> 00:29:54,300
He shouldn't have shot.

334
00:29:54,383 --> 00:29:56,385
The place is crawling
with tree niggers.

335
00:29:56,468 --> 00:29:58,804
HENRY: That's enough!
That's enough!

336
00:29:58,887 --> 00:30:00,806
We're still
in Ree territory.

337
00:30:00,889 --> 00:30:02,641
He's one of our own men.

338
00:30:02,725 --> 00:30:04,393
(CONTINUES WHEEZING)

339
00:30:04,518 --> 00:30:06,812
Scout a circle around us.
North and west.

340
00:30:06,895 --> 00:30:08,605
Take those two with you.

341
00:30:08,689 --> 00:30:10,482
Bill, Fryman,
you take south and east.

342
00:30:10,566 --> 00:30:13,068
Watch for anyone
that might've heard that shot.

343
00:30:13,527 --> 00:30:15,237
We have to stitch him up.

344
00:30:15,404 --> 00:30:18,324
What about me? Captain?

345
00:30:18,407 --> 00:30:19,867
You just stay here.

346
00:30:20,326 --> 00:30:21,327
Hold it down.

347
00:30:21,744 --> 00:30:22,786
JIM:
I'm so sorry, Mr. Glass.

348
00:30:22,870 --> 00:30:25,497
HENRY: Bridger,
press down here.

349
00:30:26,498 --> 00:30:28,083
JIM: He's bleeding
down here, too.

350
00:30:28,208 --> 00:30:29,418
(GLASS SCREAMING)

351
00:30:29,543 --> 00:30:31,795
ANDERSON:
They're torturing the bastard.

352
00:30:31,879 --> 00:30:33,714
The proper thing to do
would be...

353
00:30:34,048 --> 00:30:35,924
...to finish him off quick.

354
00:30:36,383 --> 00:30:38,927
Unless he has a chance
of pulling through.

355
00:30:39,428 --> 00:30:40,721
(SCOFFS)

356
00:30:40,888 --> 00:30:42,556
Pulling through?

357
00:30:42,890 --> 00:30:44,892
You saw what that
grizz did to him.

358
00:30:45,017 --> 00:30:47,061
He'll be dead
inside an hour.
Mmm-hmm.

359
00:30:48,395 --> 00:30:51,940
Yeah, we all will be
if he don't quit
wailing like that.

360
00:30:54,693 --> 00:30:57,988
Toward you and twist it
into place. I'll hold him. Go.

361
00:30:58,072 --> 00:30:59,865
Pa.
HENRY: Hold him. Go.

362
00:31:01,075 --> 00:31:02,117
Go!

363
00:31:02,576 --> 00:31:03,702
Now!

364
00:31:08,749 --> 00:31:10,417
He passed out.

365
00:31:11,251 --> 00:31:13,921
I'll take advantage
and stitch up his neck.

366
00:31:15,089 --> 00:31:16,131
Water.

367
00:31:23,972 --> 00:31:24,973
Bridger, tell the others

368
00:31:25,099 --> 00:31:26,266
we'll camp here tonight.
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

369
00:31:26,517 --> 00:31:28,727
I'm right here.

370
00:31:29,645 --> 00:31:32,898
I'll be right here...

371
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:35,317
(MEN LAUGHING)

372
00:31:36,985 --> 00:31:38,487
(MEN SPEAKING FRENCH)

373
00:31:46,328 --> 00:31:47,913
Toussaint, he's here.

374
00:31:48,455 --> 00:31:51,041
I thought he wouldn't make it.

375
00:31:52,835 --> 00:31:55,754
I'm glad you made it here.

376
00:31:56,338 --> 00:31:59,133
We need horses and rifles.

377
00:31:59,758 --> 00:32:01,844
We bring you many pelts.

378
00:32:02,094 --> 00:32:06,473
No horses... just what we agreed.

379
00:32:07,307 --> 00:32:09,518
Take all the pelts you want.

380
00:32:09,935 --> 00:32:12,813
We need horses and rifles.

381
00:32:13,188 --> 00:32:16,108
I need a woman with big tits...

382
00:32:16,191 --> 00:32:17,901
Who can cook.

383
00:32:18,527 --> 00:32:20,863
We can't give you any horses.

384
00:32:22,030 --> 00:32:23,031
What's he saying?

385
00:32:23,031 --> 00:32:24,867
I don't know, something about horses.

386
00:32:24,867 --> 00:32:26,994
Bring us something to drink... some whisky.

387
00:32:28,454 --> 00:32:30,706
Tell him to stop asking about the horses.

388
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:34,543
Always good doing business with you.

389
00:32:35,002 --> 00:32:36,378
Horses.

390
00:32:36,879 --> 00:32:38,046
No horses.

391
00:32:39,214 --> 00:32:40,924
All we can trade are guns and ammunition.

392
00:32:41,717 --> 00:32:45,429
Tell him if he asks about horses again,
there is no deal.

393
00:32:46,013 --> 00:32:49,266
Where did you get these? The Americans?

394
00:32:49,892 --> 00:32:51,393
They're already branded.

395
00:32:51,894 --> 00:32:55,731
I'll only be able to get half price for them.

396
00:32:56,732 --> 00:32:58,775
Get him away from there.

397
00:32:58,901 --> 00:33:00,360
I said no horses.

398
00:33:01,069 --> 00:33:03,113
We'll take these three horses.

399
00:33:03,405 --> 00:33:04,948
I'm not going to say it again.

400
00:33:05,073 --> 00:33:06,700
They aren't part of the deal.

401
00:33:06,700 --> 00:33:08,368
Now tell your man to step away.

402
00:33:08,494 --> 00:33:11,288
We had an agreement, you have to honor it.

403
00:33:11,872 --> 00:33:17,085
in French
You stand there and talk to me about honor?

404
00:33:17,586 --> 00:33:20,422
I told you he speaks French.

405
00:33:21,924 --> 00:33:24,009
Those pelts are stolen.

406
00:33:28,055 --> 00:33:31,767
You all have stolen everything from us.

407
00:33:34,019 --> 00:33:35,646
Everything!

408
00:33:35,938 --> 00:33:37,356
The land.

409
00:33:37,773 --> 00:33:39,816
The animals.

410
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:49,785
Two white men snuck into our village,
and took my daughter, Powaqa.

411
00:33:49,785 --> 00:33:54,790
We leave you these pelts
because honor demands it.

412
00:33:54,790 --> 00:33:58,001
I take your horses to find my daughter.

413
00:33:58,001 --> 00:34:01,797
You are free to try and stop me.

414
00:34:05,592 --> 00:34:09,012
Business is business.

415
00:34:11,473 --> 00:34:14,977
Prepare five horses for them.

416
00:34:20,899 --> 00:34:23,735
HENRY: I want everybody up
at the crack of dawn.

417
00:34:24,486 --> 00:34:26,572
Carrying Glass will be hard...

418
00:34:26,822 --> 00:34:29,741
...80 we need to get ahead
as far as possible.

419
00:34:30,742 --> 00:34:32,578
We'll divide into two groups.

420
00:34:33,078 --> 00:34:35,664
Fitzgerald, Jones, Fryman,

421
00:34:35,789 --> 00:34:38,083
you take the east side
of the river.

422
00:34:38,166 --> 00:34:40,586
Anderson, you scout up front.

423
00:34:40,669 --> 00:34:43,005
That claw
don't belong to you.

424
00:34:45,674 --> 00:34:47,175
It ain't for me.

425
00:35:04,776 --> 00:35:06,486
(WHEEZING)

426
00:35:09,406 --> 00:35:11,241
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

427
00:35:20,876 --> 00:35:22,586
(MEN ARGUING)

428
00:35:33,138 --> 00:35:34,556
Stop!

429
00:35:44,441 --> 00:35:46,068
(HAWK SPEAKING PAWNEE)

430
00:35:48,737 --> 00:35:50,113
(COUGHING)

431
00:36:01,792 --> 00:36:05,253
HENRY: Don't let him down!
Don't let him down!

432
00:36:16,807 --> 00:36:18,141
ANDERSON: Watch it.

433
00:36:18,725 --> 00:36:19,935
JONES: How we gonna
make it up this?

434
00:36:20,018 --> 00:36:21,144
FITZGERALD: Slow down.

435
00:36:21,228 --> 00:36:23,814
ANDERSON:
It's killing us, Captain!

436
00:36:24,356 --> 00:36:25,565
(ALL GRUNTING)

437
00:36:30,779 --> 00:36:32,614
HENRY: Lift it, Bridger!

438
00:36:33,448 --> 00:36:35,367
FITZGERALD: Goddamn it,
keep it steady.

439
00:36:35,450 --> 00:36:36,493
JIM: Lift it up higher.

440
00:36:36,576 --> 00:36:37,619
HAWK: I am.

441
00:36:39,454 --> 00:36:40,956
HENRY: And heave!

442
00:36:41,039 --> 00:36:42,207
(ALL GROAN)

443
00:36:42,290 --> 00:36:44,376
JONES: I'll go up and pull.

444
00:36:46,128 --> 00:36:47,295
(ALL GRUNTING)

445
00:36:48,296 --> 00:36:49,548
(ALL EXCLAIM)

446
00:36:50,882 --> 00:36:52,759
My foot!

447
00:36:52,843 --> 00:36:54,511
Enough of this shit!

448
00:36:54,636 --> 00:36:57,305
We'll never make it across
like this, Captain.

449
00:36:57,639 --> 00:36:59,307
He's burning up.
(COUGHING)

450
00:36:59,391 --> 00:37:00,600
(ALL PANTING)

451
00:37:01,226 --> 00:37:04,312
Cap'n, you ain't doing us
nor him no favors...

452
00:37:04,396 --> 00:37:06,857
...by letting him
go on suffering like this.

453
00:37:08,483 --> 00:37:11,153
Captain, it's all
the same up here.

454
00:37:11,236 --> 00:37:14,740
We're gonna have to go back.
Find another way.

455
00:37:14,823 --> 00:37:16,408
(GLASS WHEEZING)

456
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:24,416
Glass. Hugh.

457
00:37:25,584 --> 00:37:27,919
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

458
00:37:28,587 --> 00:37:30,922
Lay that rag over his eyes,
Mr. Bridger.

459
00:37:31,131 --> 00:37:32,215
HAWK: What?

460
00:37:32,299 --> 00:37:33,467
HENRY: Lay the rag
over his eyes.

461
00:37:33,550 --> 00:37:34,676
HAWK: Wait!

462
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:35,927
HENRY: I'm sorry, Hugh.

463
00:37:36,011 --> 00:37:37,763
JIM: Sir, I can't do that.

464
00:37:37,846 --> 00:37:39,264
HAWK: How do we
get back without him?

465
00:37:39,347 --> 00:37:40,974
Only he knows the way.

466
00:37:41,057 --> 00:37:42,058
HENRY: Lay the rag
over his eyes.

467
00:37:42,142 --> 00:37:43,185
JIM: I can't.

468
00:37:43,268 --> 00:37:44,770
Wait! How do
we get back--

469
00:37:44,853 --> 00:37:46,313
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

470
00:37:48,774 --> 00:37:50,609
HENRY: Lay it over his eyes!

471
00:37:51,109 --> 00:37:52,611
Step back.

472
00:37:54,780 --> 00:37:57,365
HAWK: Bridger, stop!
Bridger, Henry.

473
00:37:57,449 --> 00:37:59,284
Henry! Henry, please.

474
00:37:59,618 --> 00:38:02,287
Captain. Captain.
Please. Please leave--

475
00:38:02,662 --> 00:38:04,164
(HAWK SPEAKING PAWNEE)

476
00:38:04,873 --> 00:38:06,416
(GLASS CONTINUES WHEEZING)

477
00:38:12,464 --> 00:38:13,965
There's a $70 bonus

478
00:38:14,049 --> 00:38:16,885
from the Rocky Mountain Fur
Company to the two men...

479
00:38:16,968 --> 00:38:19,221
...that stay with Glass
to see this through.

480
00:38:19,304 --> 00:38:20,388
HAWK: I'll stay!

481
00:38:20,472 --> 00:38:22,641
Me, too.
Money or not, I'll stay.

482
00:38:23,809 --> 00:38:25,310
I'll need a third.

483
00:38:25,644 --> 00:38:26,812
Sorry, Captain.

484
00:38:26,895 --> 00:38:30,148
I have a family.
I'm not crazy.

485
00:38:30,816 --> 00:38:33,735
Captain, three men
can't hold off
a party of Ree,

486
00:38:33,819 --> 00:38:35,654
much less some boys.

487
00:38:35,987 --> 00:38:39,074
Besides, $70 ain't gonna buy
nobody a new set of ears.

488
00:38:39,157 --> 00:38:40,742
A hundred, then.

489
00:38:41,326 --> 00:38:43,578
This man is the only reason
we're still alive.

490
00:38:43,662 --> 00:38:45,914
We were 45 men
when this started.

491
00:38:45,997 --> 00:38:48,083
Now we're ten. Almost nine.

492
00:38:48,416 --> 00:38:50,335
HAWK: He's my father.
He can have my share.

493
00:38:50,418 --> 00:38:52,921
JIM: Mine, too.
He can have my share also.

494
00:38:57,676 --> 00:38:58,927
All right.

495
00:38:59,427 --> 00:39:01,221
If Mr. Bridger
feels the same way,

496
00:39:01,304 --> 00:39:02,597
I'll lag behind with them.

497
00:39:02,681 --> 00:39:03,932
You?
Yep.

498
00:39:04,015 --> 00:39:06,017
You already lost
my share of the pelts...

499
00:39:06,101 --> 00:39:07,894
...S0 I got no choice
but to make it up

500
00:39:07,978 --> 00:39:09,521
by some other means.

501
00:39:09,855 --> 00:39:11,481
Sticking around
for another day or two

502
00:39:11,565 --> 00:39:13,108
don't make
no difference.

503
00:39:13,191 --> 00:39:15,694
$300...at least I get to
go home with something.

504
00:39:15,777 --> 00:39:18,697
Glass is to be cared
for until, understood?

505
00:39:19,030 --> 00:39:21,700
Yeah. You have my word.
I understand.

506
00:39:23,285 --> 00:39:24,703
HENRY: You boys get him
down off this slope

507
00:39:24,786 --> 00:39:26,705
and somewhere safe
before dark.

508
00:39:27,038 --> 00:39:28,373
Fitzgerald.

509
00:39:30,834 --> 00:39:33,378
Glass is to be cared for
as long as necessary.

510
00:39:33,712 --> 00:39:35,630
And a proper burial
when it's time.

511
00:39:35,714 --> 00:39:36,882
He's earned it.

512
00:39:37,716 --> 00:39:39,134
I understand.

513
00:39:42,387 --> 00:39:43,889
You hurt yourself?

514
00:39:44,639 --> 00:39:46,057
ANDERSON: I'll be fine.

515
00:39:50,186 --> 00:39:51,855
(GLASS WHEEZING)

516
00:39:52,772 --> 00:39:54,107
(HAWK SPEAKING PAWNEE)

517
00:39:54,232 --> 00:39:56,985
Can you hear that wind, father?

518
00:39:59,905 --> 00:40:05,285
Remember what mother used to say
about the wind?

519
00:40:06,494 --> 00:40:11,791
The wind cannot defeat
a tree with strong roots.

520
00:40:17,464 --> 00:40:21,676
You are still breathing...

521
00:40:24,304 --> 00:40:28,725
I miss her so much.

522
00:40:34,022 --> 00:40:35,982
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

523
00:40:45,617 --> 00:40:47,118
(GLASS SPEAKING PAWNEE)

524
00:40:49,204 --> 00:40:51,915
I will be right here...

525
00:40:53,375 --> 00:40:55,502
I'm right here.

526
00:40:59,881 --> 00:41:04,928
As long as you can still grab a breath,
you fight.

527
00:41:06,346 --> 00:41:08,807
You breathe. Keep breathing.

528
00:41:09,099 --> 00:41:10,225
(GLASS'S WIFE SPEAKING PAWNEE)

529
00:41:10,350 --> 00:41:13,853
When there is a storm...

530
00:41:15,605 --> 00:41:20,485
And you stand in front of a tree...

531
00:41:22,362 --> 00:41:23,613
(GUNSHOT)

532
00:41:25,532 --> 00:41:32,539
If you look at its branches,
you swear it will fall.

533
00:41:42,257 --> 00:41:51,933
But if you watch the trunk,
you will see its stability.

534
00:41:56,813 --> 00:41:58,148
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

535
00:42:08,408 --> 00:42:09,784
(FITZGERALD GRUNTING)

536
00:42:32,223 --> 00:42:33,725
FITZGERALD:
Three hundred bucks

537
00:42:33,808 --> 00:42:35,393
goes a long way
toward retirement.

538
00:42:35,727 --> 00:42:38,271
Go down to Texas, find me
a decent piece of land,

539
00:42:38,354 --> 00:42:40,231
and start pissing in the wind.

540
00:42:41,232 --> 00:42:44,402
Get me the hell out of this
godforsaken place.

541
00:42:44,486 --> 00:42:45,945
(JIM SCRAPING FLASK)

542
00:42:48,740 --> 00:42:50,408
Ree done that to you?

543
00:42:52,243 --> 00:42:53,661
I'm just asking.

544
00:42:54,662 --> 00:42:56,331
Yeah, they done it.

545
00:42:56,915 --> 00:42:59,501
They took their
sweet time with it.

546
00:43:00,585 --> 00:43:01,920
At the start,
I didn't feel nothing.

547
00:43:02,003 --> 00:43:03,755
I just heard the sound...

548
00:43:04,089 --> 00:43:07,258
...of the knife scraping
against my skull and...

549
00:43:07,592 --> 00:43:08,968
...them all laughing
and whooping

550
00:43:09,052 --> 00:43:11,096
and hollering and whatnot.

551
00:43:11,429 --> 00:43:12,931
Then the blood came.

552
00:43:13,264 --> 00:43:16,017
It was cold. It started
streaming down my face,

553
00:43:16,101 --> 00:43:17,602
in my eyes, and...

554
00:43:18,019 --> 00:43:19,604
...breathing it in.

555
00:43:20,105 --> 00:43:21,773
Choking on it.

556
00:43:22,941 --> 00:43:24,943
That's when I felt it.

557
00:43:25,443 --> 00:43:27,612
Yeah, felt all of it.

558
00:43:28,279 --> 00:43:30,782
I got my head
turned inside out.

559
00:43:31,699 --> 00:43:32,867
JIM: Jesus.

560
00:43:32,951 --> 00:43:34,953
Them Indians
down Texas way...

561
00:43:35,286 --> 00:43:38,123
...they may rob you,
but they ain't gonna
take your topknot.

562
00:43:39,374 --> 00:43:40,875
JIM: When was it?

563
00:43:44,129 --> 00:43:45,588
Goddamn it,

564
00:43:45,672 --> 00:43:48,967
will you quit that noise now,
will you?

565
00:43:49,300 --> 00:43:50,468
Quit it.

566
00:44:15,994 --> 00:44:17,620
FITZGERALD:
I'm falling further back

567
00:44:17,704 --> 00:44:20,248
from Henry and the boys
on account of tending to you.

568
00:44:24,669 --> 00:44:25,920
Got to get up
the damn mountain,

569
00:44:26,004 --> 00:44:28,339
but winter
keeps chasing us down.

570
00:44:31,176 --> 00:44:34,512
If you ready
to take the sacrament...

571
00:44:35,680 --> 00:44:37,682
...I can do that for you.

572
00:44:42,854 --> 00:44:44,939
What you holding to, Glass?

573
00:44:48,526 --> 00:44:49,694
You know...

574
00:44:50,445 --> 00:44:52,280
...it would be better...

575
00:44:52,363 --> 00:44:55,575
...iIf you were to take that
last breath of yours now...

576
00:44:55,658 --> 00:44:57,118
for all of us.

577
00:44:59,704 --> 00:45:01,539
Now you hung tough.

578
00:45:01,873 --> 00:45:03,458
And that's something.

579
00:45:04,542 --> 00:45:05,877
I'm begging you.

580
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:08,171
Them Ree are so close
I can smell 'em.

581
00:45:08,254 --> 00:45:10,548
You can smell 'em, too.

582
00:45:10,632 --> 00:45:13,051
You got to think of your boy.
All right?

583
00:45:13,134 --> 00:45:14,719
'Cause you're gonna kill him.

584
00:45:15,053 --> 00:45:17,138
You'll kill us all.

585
00:45:17,222 --> 00:45:18,514
(MUTTERING)

586
00:45:24,145 --> 00:45:26,314
I can muzzle you
if you like.

587
00:45:26,397 --> 00:45:28,316
Take away this suffering
quick and easy.

588
00:45:28,399 --> 00:45:31,402
No one ever has to know
that you give up.

589
00:45:32,570 --> 00:45:35,657
All you have to do is blink
if you want me to do that.

590
00:45:36,574 --> 00:45:38,409
(GRUNTING SOFTLY)

591
00:45:41,913 --> 00:45:44,165
Save your boy and blink.

592
00:45:53,925 --> 00:45:56,261
You just
have to blink.

593
00:46:01,266 --> 00:46:03,601
Yeah. There it is.

594
00:46:04,102 --> 00:46:05,520
You'd best hope
the good Lord'll

595
00:46:05,603 --> 00:46:07,605
get His ass here
quick, huh?

596
00:46:11,526 --> 00:46:13,861
Maybe He'll forgive your sins,
maybe not.

597
00:46:13,945 --> 00:46:16,030
Thus I do commend thee
to the Lord.

598
00:46:16,114 --> 00:46:17,532
(GLASS CHOKING)

599
00:46:17,615 --> 00:46:21,953
Through Jesus Christ the Lord
of all reality and mercy...

600
00:46:22,370 --> 00:46:25,707
...and the Father
and the Creator, I hold thee--

601
00:46:25,790 --> 00:46:28,042
Get away! Get away!

602
00:46:28,126 --> 00:46:31,629
You okay?
Jim! Jim! Help!

603
00:46:42,765 --> 00:46:43,808
HAWK: Help!

604
00:46:43,891 --> 00:46:45,226
Calm down.

605
00:46:45,310 --> 00:46:47,145
Jim! Help!

606
00:46:47,228 --> 00:46:49,897
Don't shout! You're gonna
get us all killed!

607
00:46:49,981 --> 00:46:52,358
Keep away! I'll tell
the Captain what you did.

608
00:46:52,442 --> 00:46:53,985
They'll hang you!

609
00:46:54,068 --> 00:46:56,487
They'll hang you! Jim, help!

610
00:46:56,571 --> 00:46:58,656
We have an understanding.

611
00:47:02,243 --> 00:47:04,412
What's fucking wrong
with you people?

612
00:47:04,495 --> 00:47:05,705
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

613
00:47:15,006 --> 00:47:16,341
Shit.

614
00:47:17,675 --> 00:47:19,844
(GLASS CONTINUES
MUFFLED SCREAMING)

615
00:47:30,438 --> 00:47:32,273
(CONTINUES MUFFLED SCREAMING)

616
00:48:17,235 --> 00:48:19,237
JIM:
I got one beaver, Hawk.

617
00:48:21,072 --> 00:48:22,740
Breathing changed?

618
00:48:24,409 --> 00:48:26,244
I hadn't noticed.

619
00:48:27,578 --> 00:48:29,414
Damn, he's cold as ice.

620
00:48:31,082 --> 00:48:33,084
Here you go, Mr. Glass.

621
00:48:33,167 --> 00:48:35,920
This will help you.
Keep you warm.

622
00:48:36,921 --> 00:48:38,256
It's all right.

623
00:48:40,174 --> 00:48:41,592
Where's Hawk?

624
00:48:42,927 --> 00:48:44,512
He ain't with you?

625
00:48:45,763 --> 00:48:46,848
No.

626
00:48:46,931 --> 00:48:48,266
No?

627
00:48:48,349 --> 00:48:50,143
(GLASS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

628
00:48:53,271 --> 00:48:55,356
I understand, Mr. Glass.

629
00:48:55,440 --> 00:48:58,443
It's all right.
I think I'll get a fire going.

630
00:48:58,776 --> 00:49:01,279
FITZGERALD: Yeah.
Sounds like a good idea.

631
00:49:02,238 --> 00:49:03,573
(SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

632
00:49:07,452 --> 00:49:08,786
JIM: Hawk!

633
00:49:12,123 --> 00:49:13,458
Hawk!

634
00:49:35,229 --> 00:49:36,731
FITZGERALD: Shh. Ree.

635
00:49:36,814 --> 00:49:39,734
There's about 20 of them
down by the creek.

636
00:49:39,817 --> 00:49:43,654
They're headed this way.
Grab your shit and let's go.

637
00:49:45,406 --> 00:49:47,909
Shit. What do we do?

638
00:49:47,992 --> 00:49:49,744
FITZGERALD: Run, right now.

639
00:49:49,827 --> 00:49:50,995
What about Hawk?

640
00:49:51,078 --> 00:49:52,997
He ain't our problem no more.

641
00:49:53,080 --> 00:49:54,499
We can't just leave him.

642
00:49:54,582 --> 00:49:56,250
Either he's gutted or scalped.

643
00:49:56,334 --> 00:49:58,753
And if he ain't
he can find us, can't he?

644
00:49:58,836 --> 00:50:00,671
What about Glass?

645
00:50:00,755 --> 00:50:03,132
He ain't our problem.
Like us, he's on his own.

646
00:50:03,216 --> 00:50:05,801
We made a promise
to the Captain.

647
00:50:05,885 --> 00:50:07,512
A proper burial
when the time was needed.

648
00:50:07,595 --> 00:50:09,514
He needs that rifle!

649
00:50:09,597 --> 00:50:13,935
He couldn't do nothing with it
if you tarred it to his hand.

650
00:50:14,018 --> 00:50:15,770
We can't do this.

651
00:50:15,853 --> 00:50:17,522
We got no fucking choice.

652
00:50:17,605 --> 00:50:19,524
JIM: No, we can't.
Look at him.

653
00:50:21,692 --> 00:50:24,028
All right, shit, then, buddy.
Get him up.

654
00:50:24,111 --> 00:50:25,446
You want to take him?

655
00:50:25,530 --> 00:50:27,281
(GLASS GROANING)

656
00:50:28,199 --> 00:50:29,700
Come on now!

657
00:50:29,867 --> 00:50:32,787
JIM: Easy. Slowly, Fitz.
Easy with him.

658
00:50:34,038 --> 00:50:35,122
(JIM GROANS)

659
00:50:35,206 --> 00:50:36,832
FITZGERALD:
Just get your shit.

660
00:50:36,916 --> 00:50:38,376
Get your shit!
(GLASS SCREAMING)

661
00:50:39,210 --> 00:50:40,545
Shut up.

662
00:50:44,382 --> 00:50:45,800
Shut up!

663
00:50:46,384 --> 00:50:47,552
JIM: Hold up!

664
00:50:49,053 --> 00:50:50,304
(GLASS GROANING)

665
00:50:50,388 --> 00:50:52,557
Fitz. What are you doing?

666
00:50:52,640 --> 00:50:54,350
What does it look like?

667
00:50:54,433 --> 00:50:56,727
Proper burial.
Like you wanted.

668
00:50:56,811 --> 00:50:58,646
JIM: No, not like this.

669
00:50:58,729 --> 00:50:59,897
FITZGERALD: Why not?

670
00:51:00,690 --> 00:51:03,401
He's alive, Fitz.
He's alive.

671
00:51:05,570 --> 00:51:06,904
So shoot him.

672
00:51:09,865 --> 00:51:11,284
(GLASS SHOUTING)

673
00:51:19,834 --> 00:51:21,836
I have to go.
I have to go.

674
00:51:22,920 --> 00:51:25,256
I'm sorry, Mr. Glass.
I'm sorry.

675
00:51:26,173 --> 00:51:27,925
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
(PROTESTING INDISTINCTLY)

676
00:51:30,386 --> 00:51:32,179
(WHEEZING)

677
00:51:34,724 --> 00:51:35,975
(JIM GROANS)

678
00:51:42,440 --> 00:51:44,609
MURPHY: Captain! This way!

679
00:51:45,610 --> 00:51:48,112
There's a path down here!

680
00:51:49,780 --> 00:51:51,616
ANDERSON:
There ain't shit down there!

681
00:51:51,699 --> 00:51:53,117
We got to climb over!

682
00:51:53,200 --> 00:51:54,660
JONES:
Glass said to stay east!

683
00:51:54,744 --> 00:51:57,121
ANDERSON:
Glass can go to hell!

684
00:51:57,955 --> 00:51:59,373
HENRY: What's the map say?

685
00:51:59,457 --> 00:52:01,792
Keep climbing.
We climb, Captain.

686
00:52:01,876 --> 00:52:03,544
We keep climbing.

687
00:52:03,628 --> 00:52:05,463
Till we reach Old Gabe.

688
00:52:09,634 --> 00:52:10,968
We climb.

689
00:52:12,303 --> 00:52:13,804
We got to wait for Murph.

690
00:52:14,138 --> 00:52:15,806
ANDERSON: Yeah.
You wait for him.

691
00:52:16,641 --> 00:52:17,975
Captain?

692
00:52:20,978 --> 00:52:22,229
Sir...

693
00:52:22,313 --> 00:52:24,690
...Murphy says
there's a way down there.

694
00:52:24,774 --> 00:52:26,233
Who we following?

695
00:52:26,317 --> 00:52:27,818
ANDERSON:
You follow who you want!

696
00:52:27,902 --> 00:52:29,403
I'm going up!

697
00:52:30,488 --> 00:52:31,989
Stubby, keep going up!

698
00:52:32,073 --> 00:52:34,325
JONES: Murph! Come here!

699
00:52:53,844 --> 00:52:55,471
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

700
00:53:08,317 --> 00:53:10,069
(PANTING)

701
00:53:21,539 --> 00:53:22,915
(SCREAMS)

702
00:53:27,795 --> 00:53:29,797
(WHEEZING)

703
00:53:35,511 --> 00:53:36,971
(GRUNTING LOUDLY)

704
00:53:37,221 --> 00:53:38,931
(GASPING)

705
00:54:10,045 --> 00:54:11,672
(GRUNTING)

706
00:54:18,888 --> 00:54:20,806
(PANTING)

707
00:54:42,453 --> 00:54:43,746
(GRUNTING)

708
00:55:55,025 --> 00:55:56,235
(SPEAKING PAWNEE)

709
00:55:56,360 --> 00:56:00,406
I'm not leaving you, son.

710
00:56:02,366 --> 00:56:04,952
I'm right here.

711
00:57:10,935 --> 00:57:12,436
FITZGERALD: Fire's done.

712
00:57:13,270 --> 00:57:15,439
I can't even feel my feet.

713
00:57:17,608 --> 00:57:20,527
Didn't we put enough distance
between us and them Ree?

714
00:57:20,611 --> 00:57:23,656
A dozen Ree can make
twice as good time as we can.

715
00:57:23,739 --> 00:57:25,491
Twenty.
What?

716
00:57:27,618 --> 00:57:29,286
You said you saw
twenty Ree.

717
00:57:29,370 --> 00:57:31,622
Yeah? What you
talking about?

718
00:57:34,792 --> 00:57:36,377
You woke me up.
Mmm-hmm.

719
00:57:37,628 --> 00:57:39,880
You said you saw
twenty Ree by the creek.

720
00:57:39,964 --> 00:57:41,966
Well, yeah,
twenty, a dozen...

721
00:57:42,049 --> 00:57:43,133
...it don't matter.

722
00:57:43,217 --> 00:57:46,804
I wasn't gonna hang around
counting fucking feathers.

723
00:57:49,807 --> 00:57:51,225
As a matter of fact...

724
00:57:52,977 --> 00:57:55,729
...what was you doing down
by the creek all by yourself?

725
00:57:56,563 --> 00:57:58,774
I'd already brought up
plenty of water.

726
00:58:00,442 --> 00:58:01,735
Hey!

727
00:58:02,736 --> 00:58:05,239
Answer me, Fitzgerald.
I asked you a question.

728
00:58:06,573 --> 00:58:09,535
Don't question me
on account of you feel guilty.

729
00:58:09,618 --> 00:58:11,870
Answer me
or I'll blow your head off.

730
00:58:11,954 --> 00:58:14,123
You got
a short-term memory, boy.

731
00:58:14,623 --> 00:58:16,917
Your ass would be
floating around the Missouri
right now

732
00:58:17,001 --> 00:58:18,627
if it wasn't for me.

733
00:58:20,629 --> 00:58:22,631
You want to ask questions?

734
00:58:22,756 --> 00:58:25,092
What you want to ask?
If you want to know, ask it.

735
00:58:25,300 --> 00:58:26,552
Hmm?

736
00:58:26,635 --> 00:58:27,970
You want to know
why you left

737
00:58:28,095 --> 00:58:30,222
Mr. Glass back there
for dead, huh?

738
00:58:30,305 --> 00:58:33,559
Or why you left
your little boyfriend
running around?

739
00:58:33,642 --> 00:58:36,478
You want to know
if he's still alive?

740
00:58:36,854 --> 00:58:39,023
I'll tell you why.
It's 'cause you ain't
a man yet.

741
00:58:39,356 --> 00:58:41,316
It's 'cause you was
scared shitless.

742
00:58:41,400 --> 00:58:42,860
You're scared now.

743
00:58:42,943 --> 00:58:44,278
The Ree.

744
00:58:44,361 --> 00:58:45,696
What of them?

745
00:58:46,530 --> 00:58:48,449
Tell me, did you see 'em?

746
00:58:48,532 --> 00:58:50,701
Put your rifle down.
Did you see the Ree?

747
00:58:52,870 --> 00:58:54,121
No.

748
00:58:55,372 --> 00:58:57,207
Not a single one.

749
00:58:59,793 --> 00:59:03,380
You fucking lied to me?
You lied to me!

750
00:59:03,464 --> 00:59:04,798
(COUGHS)

751
00:59:05,132 --> 00:59:06,467
(GASPS)

752
00:59:07,134 --> 00:59:09,720
I had to scare
some sense into you, boy.

753
00:59:10,054 --> 00:59:12,222
Glass was dead.
Hawk we don't know about.

754
00:59:12,556 --> 00:59:15,225
No point in either of us
dying either, you understand?

755
00:59:15,559 --> 00:59:17,686
The way I see it,
I saved your life twice now.

756
00:59:17,770 --> 00:59:19,897
I ought to be God to you.

757
00:59:20,564 --> 00:59:23,734
And God giveth...
and God taketh away.

758
00:59:26,904 --> 00:59:28,405
(GUN CLICKS)
(GASPS)

759
00:59:31,158 --> 00:59:32,534
Lucky fucker.

760
00:59:33,911 --> 00:59:37,206
Next time you want to
shoot somebody...

761
00:59:37,289 --> 00:59:39,124
...you might
want to use powder,

762
00:59:39,208 --> 00:59:40,751
prime your rifle.

763
00:59:43,754 --> 00:59:47,424
Come on. Let's git.
Grab your shit.

764
00:59:48,759 --> 00:59:50,094
(SNIFFLES)

765
01:01:22,352 --> 01:01:23,687
(GRUNTS)

766
01:02:12,277 --> 01:02:14,404
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

767
01:02:53,819 --> 01:02:55,821
(GLASS GRUNTING)

768
01:03:44,870 --> 01:03:46,246
(SNIFFS)

769
01:03:47,080 --> 01:03:48,415
(SPEAKING ARIKARA)

770
01:03:48,582 --> 01:03:52,669
Fresh blood. This could be Powaqga.

771
01:04:04,431 --> 01:04:05,724
A dead boy.

772
01:04:14,649 --> 01:04:16,443
A Pawnee boy.

773
01:04:16,693 --> 01:04:18,195
Let's go.

774
01:04:22,616 --> 01:04:24,076
(GRUNTING)

775
01:05:01,238 --> 01:05:03,073
(PANTING)

776
01:05:28,723 --> 01:05:30,559
(COUGHING)

777
01:06:45,050 --> 01:06:46,635
(COUGHS)

778
01:07:08,615 --> 01:07:11,409
(SCREAMING)

779
01:07:29,636 --> 01:07:31,179
(ALL PANTING)

780
01:08:10,760 --> 01:08:12,304
