And this one time he head on
up the old Saba hills.

826
01:16:50,321 --> 01:16:51,864
San Saba hills?

827
01:16:52,532 --> 01:16:56,202
He joined a couple Texas
Ranger buddies of his to hunt.

828
01:16:56,536 --> 01:16:59,705
Pretty routine. He done it
like a hundred times before.

829
01:16:59,789 --> 01:17:02,750
Should have been a 3-day Kill,
but on the second day,

830
01:17:02,834 --> 01:17:04,710
it all went fucked.

831
01:17:05,211 --> 01:17:07,463
Somehow that night
he lost his buddies.

832
01:17:07,547 --> 01:17:09,215
And to top it off...

833
01:17:09,549 --> 01:17:12,051
...them Comanches
went and took the horses.

834
01:17:12,802 --> 01:17:15,304
So he was starving
and delirious...

835
01:17:15,555 --> 01:17:19,225
...and he crawls up
into this mott, this...

836
01:17:19,559 --> 01:17:21,811
...group of trees out
in the middle of nowhere

837
01:17:21,894 --> 01:17:24,480
just sticking up
in this ocean of scrub...

838
01:17:24,730 --> 01:17:26,899
...and he found religion.

839
01:17:27,817 --> 01:17:30,570
At that moment,
he told me...

840
01:17:30,903 --> 01:17:32,738
...he found God.

841
01:17:34,740 --> 01:17:35,908
Uh-huh.

842
01:17:39,412 --> 01:17:42,748
And it turns out that God...

843
01:17:43,833 --> 01:17:45,501
...He's a squirrel.

844
01:17:46,586 --> 01:17:49,255
Yeah. A big, old meaty one.

845
01:17:51,841 --> 01:17:54,427
"I found God,"
he used to say.

846
01:17:55,511 --> 01:17:58,514
"And while sitting there
and basking in the glory

847
