(YELLING)

1039
01:50:10,152 --> 01:50:11,987
(SCREAMING)

1040
01:50:44,937 --> 01:50:46,188
(GROANING)

1041
01:51:27,771 --> 01:51:30,274
(GRUNTING)

1042
01:52:42,554 --> 01:52:44,390
(SIGHING)

1043
01:53:41,822 --> 01:53:43,240
(GRUNTING)

1044
01:53:52,416 --> 01:53:53,751
(SIGHS)

1045
01:56:30,782 --> 01:56:33,869
GUARD: Fryman!
White man at the gate!

1046
01:56:40,709 --> 01:56:41,877
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1047
01:56:46,465 --> 01:56:47,799
Speak English.

1048
01:56:48,050 --> 01:56:50,177
I have no weapon.

1049
01:56:50,260 --> 01:56:51,970
(SPEAKING FRENCH)
Open her up!

1050
01:56:52,054 --> 01:56:53,472
Get the Captain!

1051
01:56:53,555 --> 01:56:54,598
HENRY: Where are your men?

1052
01:56:55,807 --> 01:56:57,017
All dead.

1053
01:56:57,100 --> 01:56:58,352
Who was he?

1054
01:56:58,894 --> 01:57:01,480
I don't know.
Something to eat, please?

1055
01:57:01,563 --> 01:57:03,106
Food comes at a price.

1056
01:57:04,316 --> 01:57:05,651
I have no money.

1057
01:57:05,734 --> 01:57:07,236
Then you don't eat.

1058
01:57:07,319 --> 01:57:10,072
Give back some of them
stolen pelts you buy
from the Injuns.

1059
01:57:10,155 --> 01:57:11,657
Not now, Jones.
Huh?

1060
01:57:11,740 --> 01:57:13,742
Silver.
How is this? Silver.

1061
01:57:16,828 --> 01:57:18,247
This all you got?

1062
01:57:20,332 --> 01:57:22,334
We was nine.

1063
01:57:22,668 --> 01:57:25,170
My friend, he die
in the snow.

1064
01:57:25,504 --> 01:57:27,506
And the other was...

1065
01:57:27,839 --> 01:57:29,841
...Kill by wolf. I see it.

1066
01:57:30,175 --> 01:57:32,344
By wolf, yeah, Kill.

1067
01:57:32,678 --> 01:57:34,263
Where'd you get this?

1068
01:57:34,846 --> 01:57:36,181
Canteen.

1069
01:57:36,431 --> 01:57:39,184
He drop it.
He kill Toussaint,
he drop it--

1070
01:57:39,268 --> 01:57:40,477
Who? Who?

1071
01:57:40,561 --> 01:57:42,688
I don't know.
I don't see.

1072
01:57:44,606 --> 01:57:45,649
It could be Hawk.

1073
01:57:48,527 --> 01:57:49,945
Yeah, could be.

1074
01:57:50,028 --> 01:57:52,114
JONES: That half-breed runt
couldn't steal no horse.

1075
01:57:52,197 --> 01:57:53,907
Maybe it was Weston.
STUBBY BILL: Or Beckett.

1076
01:57:53,991 --> 01:57:55,367
How far from here?

1077
01:57:55,450 --> 01:57:56,785
(STAMMERS) Thirty mile.

1078
01:57:56,868 --> 01:57:58,495
Northwest,
near the Yellowstone.

1079
01:57:58,579 --> 01:57:59,955
The Yellowstone!

1080
01:58:00,038 --> 01:58:02,708
Get the horses saddled.
Torches and supplies.

1081
01:58:02,791 --> 01:58:04,543
Ten dollars a man.

1082
01:58:04,626 --> 01:58:06,211
Anderson, you stay here.

1083
01:58:06,295 --> 01:58:09,172
ANDERSON: Yes, sir.
Feed him and watch him.

1084
01:58:10,465 --> 01:58:12,009
I'll get you a drink.

1085
01:58:23,270 --> 01:58:25,147
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1086
01:58:28,108 --> 01:58:29,192
HENRY: When we get to
the Yellowstone,

1087
01:58:29,318 --> 01:58:31,445
we split into two groups!

1088
01:58:42,873 --> 01:58:44,207
HENRY: Hawk!

1089
01:58:44,458 --> 01:58:46,460
JIM: Hawk, you out there?

1090
01:58:52,549 --> 01:58:53,675
(GUNSHOT)

1091
01:58:54,051 --> 01:58:56,219
Whoa! Whoa!
(HORSES WHINNYING)

1092
01:59:03,352 --> 01:59:05,145
HENRY: Keep your guard up!

1093
01:59:06,897 --> 01:59:08,398
Eyes in front!

1094
01:59:20,035 --> 01:59:21,495
Who are you?

1095
01:59:21,745 --> 01:59:23,580
FRYMAN: Beckett? Is that you?

1096
01:59:27,584 --> 01:59:29,753
(MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

1097
01:59:35,342 --> 01:59:36,510
HENRY: Glass?

1098
01:59:37,761 --> 01:59:38,804
Glass!

1099
01:59:39,513 --> 01:59:41,139
Jesus Christ!

1100
01:59:41,223 --> 01:59:43,100
Jesus Christ,
what happened?

1101
01:59:43,767 --> 01:59:45,352
Where is he?

1102
01:59:45,435 --> 01:59:47,437
(WHEEZING)

1103
01:59:48,188 --> 01:59:50,524
HENRY: Jones, take him. Go.

1104
01:59:51,024 --> 01:59:53,860
I'm riding ahead.
Bill, take Bridger.

1105
01:59:54,861 --> 01:59:56,363
Take Bridger!

1106
02:00:10,544 --> 02:00:11,545
Have you seen Fitzgerald?

1107
02:00:11,628 --> 02:00:12,963
No, sir.

1108
02:00:18,802 --> 02:00:20,971
Get up. Get up!

1109
02:00:21,054 --> 02:00:22,806
You seen Fitzgerald?
No, sir.

1110
02:00:22,973 --> 02:00:24,057
Fitzgerald?

1111
02:00:33,900 --> 02:00:36,695
Whoa, easy.
Where did he go?

1112
02:00:37,904 --> 02:00:40,407
Who?
Fitzgerald. Where did he go?

1113
02:00:40,741 --> 02:00:41,742
I have no idea.

1114
02:00:41,825 --> 02:00:43,285
Tell me or I'll take
your head off.

1115
02:00:43,368 --> 02:00:45,328
I swear to God-- (GROANS)

1116
02:00:45,412 --> 02:00:47,330
Tell me. Tell me!

1117
02:00:47,414 --> 02:00:48,707
Texas!

1118
02:00:48,790 --> 02:00:53,086
He said he was going to Texas.
He said he was gonna reenlist.

1119
02:00:53,170 --> 02:00:54,588
Then he started
talking about property.

1120
02:00:54,671 --> 02:00:56,590
"A decent
piece of land."

1121
02:00:56,673 --> 02:00:59,217
He's heading for Texas.
That's all I know.

1122
02:00:59,301 --> 02:01:00,635
Stay here.

1123
02:01:03,764 --> 02:01:05,265
Fitzgerald!

1124
02:01:06,600 --> 02:01:08,268
Fitzgerald!

1125
02:01:24,868 --> 02:01:26,286
(METAL CLANKING)

1126
02:01:27,204 --> 02:01:28,872
(OBJECT CLATTERS)

1127
02:01:33,043 --> 02:01:34,211
(GASPS)

1128
02:01:36,797 --> 02:01:38,298
Goddamn it!

1129
02:01:41,051 --> 02:01:42,636
Goddamn it!

1130
02:01:43,303 --> 02:01:46,223
GUARD: Jones! Get the Captain!

1131
02:01:46,306 --> 02:01:47,474
Fryman!

1132
02:01:47,557 --> 02:01:48,725
JONES: Open the gate!

1133
02:01:48,809 --> 02:01:50,310
GUARD: Open it up!

1134
02:01:52,103 --> 02:01:53,730
JONES: Murphy,
get the Captain.

1135
02:02:00,153 --> 02:02:02,739
Get him to the doctor. Now!

1136
02:02:03,907 --> 02:02:07,577
You said he was dead!
You said he was dead!

1137
02:02:07,661 --> 02:02:08,745
I thought
he was, I swear!

1138
02:02:08,829 --> 02:02:09,913
(HENRY GRUNTING)

1139
02:02:10,664 --> 02:02:11,998
JIM: He lied to me!

1140
02:02:12,082 --> 02:02:13,500
HENRY: You're a liar.

1141
02:02:13,583 --> 02:02:16,127
You left him out there!

1142
02:02:17,170 --> 02:02:18,922
Say the Lord's Prayer.

1143
02:02:19,256 --> 02:02:21,174
Say the Lord's Prayer!

1144
02:02:22,509 --> 02:02:27,013
Our Father, Who art in heaven.
Who art-- (SOBBING) I can't!

1145
02:02:27,097 --> 02:02:28,849
Shut up! Shut up!

1146
02:02:28,932 --> 02:02:31,852
From here out,
you're a prisoner
charged with treason!

1147
02:02:31,935 --> 02:02:34,563
Take him to the cage!
Take him to the cage

1148
02:02:34,646 --> 02:02:36,523
or you'll hang
alongside him!

1149
02:02:36,606 --> 02:02:38,775
I thought he was gonna die!

1150
02:02:40,193 --> 02:02:41,945
Fitz lied to me!

1151
02:02:43,029 --> 02:02:44,281
I couldn't help him!

1152
02:02:48,201 --> 02:02:49,619
Glass!

1153
02:02:49,703 --> 02:02:51,413
Fitz lied to me!

1154
02:03:00,714 --> 02:03:01,965
(ALL GRUNTING)

1155
02:03:03,133 --> 02:03:05,927
(DOGS BARKING)

1156
02:03:06,970 --> 02:03:08,221
(GLASS BREATHING HEAVILY)

1157
02:03:21,902 --> 02:03:22,903
How is he?

1158
02:03:22,986 --> 02:03:24,404
DOCTOR: He'll be fine,
but there is swelling.

1159
02:03:24,487 --> 02:03:25,822
He needs to rest.

1160
02:03:25,947 --> 02:03:27,991
I'll be back
to check up on him.

1161
02:03:37,334 --> 02:03:39,586
GLASS: He ran off,
didn't he?

1162
02:03:48,178 --> 02:03:50,513
Bridger's telling the truth.

1163
02:03:52,349 --> 02:03:53,683
How's that?

1164
02:03:54,267 --> 02:03:58,021
Fitzgerald lied to him.
He was just following orders.

1165
02:04:00,106 --> 02:04:02,901
He wasn't there when
Fitzgerald stabbed
my boy to death.

1166
02:04:07,948 --> 02:04:09,532
Is that what happened?

1167
02:04:11,785 --> 02:04:13,286
He killed Hawk.

1168
02:04:17,374 --> 02:04:18,959
I need a horse and gun.

1169
02:04:19,042 --> 02:04:22,420
No, you need to rest and eat.
I'm going after him.

1170
02:04:22,504 --> 02:04:23,755
No.

1171
02:04:25,131 --> 02:04:26,800
You'll never find him
without me.

1172
02:04:27,133 --> 02:04:29,803
If we wait till morning
he'll get away.

1173
02:04:29,886 --> 02:04:31,471
No, he won't.

1174
02:04:32,639 --> 02:04:34,474
He's afraid.

1175
02:04:35,475 --> 02:04:38,478
He knows how far
I came for him.

1176
02:04:39,729 --> 02:04:40,730
Same as that elk.

1177
02:04:40,814 --> 02:04:44,234
When they get afraid,
they run deep into the woods.

1178
02:04:44,818 --> 02:04:48,697
I got him trapped.
He just doesn't know it yet.

1179
02:04:49,072 --> 02:04:50,907
How can you be so sure?

1180
02:04:51,741 --> 02:04:54,577
'Cause he has
everything to lose.

1181
02:04:56,663 --> 02:04:59,165
All I had was that boy.

1182
02:05:00,333 --> 02:05:02,502
And he took him away from me.

1183
02:05:05,922 --> 02:05:08,258
I can't let you
go back out there.

1184
02:05:08,341 --> 02:05:09,926
Not again.

1185
02:05:13,179 --> 02:05:15,849
I ain't afraid
to die anymore.

1186
02:05:17,559 --> 02:05:19,436
I done it already.

1187
02:05:25,191 --> 02:05:27,110
I'm going with you.

1188
02:05:53,011 --> 02:05:54,846
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1189
02:06:21,331 --> 02:06:22,749
(SIGHS)

1190
02:06:23,958 --> 02:06:25,627
(DOGS BARKING)

1191
02:06:30,173 --> 02:06:33,009
(GLASS URGING HORSE)

1192
02:06:42,352 --> 02:06:44,312
GLASS: That's his horse,
all right.

1193
02:06:46,940 --> 02:06:49,734
No way he could've ridden him
through the night.

1194
02:06:49,818 --> 02:06:51,528
HENRY: How far ahead?

1195
02:06:52,112 --> 02:06:54,114
Half a day at the most.

1196
02:06:54,447 --> 02:06:56,199
Could be Ree.

1197
02:06:56,324 --> 02:06:58,618
If they aren't his,
we lose him.

1198
02:06:59,285 --> 02:07:02,956
Unless he reenlisted
so he could justify
killing again...

1199
02:07:03,289 --> 02:07:05,291
...these tracks
right here are his.

1200
02:07:05,375 --> 02:07:07,544
(GLASS URGING HORSE)

1201
02:07:15,635 --> 02:07:18,138
HENRY: I can't remember
my wife's face.

1202
02:07:18,972 --> 02:07:21,474
Last week,
she was still with me.

1203
02:07:23,059 --> 02:07:24,811
Now she's gone.

1204
02:07:27,814 --> 02:07:31,151
I worry I won't recognize her
when I get back home.

1205
02:07:43,329 --> 02:07:45,665
Is it true
you killed an officer?

1206
02:07:50,336 --> 02:07:53,673
I just killed the man
who was trying
to kill my son.

1207
02:08:08,438 --> 02:08:09,772
(SNIFFING)

1208
02:08:12,442 --> 02:08:13,776
Smoke.

1209
02:08:15,028 --> 02:08:16,446
How close?

1210
02:08:21,117 --> 02:08:23,369
No more than
a mile up that way.

1211
02:08:23,536 --> 02:08:26,873
I'm gonna head up to the west.
You go down to the east.

1212
02:08:27,207 --> 02:08:29,626
Let's see if we can
find some tracks.

1213
02:08:30,501 --> 02:08:32,295
And if it's the Ree?

1214
02:08:32,795 --> 02:08:35,215
If it's the Ree,
you turn right back around

1215
02:08:35,298 --> 02:08:37,133
and meet me back here.
(URGES HORSE)

1216
02:09:33,022 --> 02:09:36,025
(GLASS'S WIFE SPEAKING PAWNEE)

1217
02:10:04,971 --> 02:10:07,807
Now, I wouldn't expect
to find a man
of your stature...

1218
02:10:08,141 --> 02:10:09,642
...80 far away
from his stove

1219
02:10:09,726 --> 02:10:11,394
on a morning
as cold as this, Captain.

1220
02:10:11,477 --> 02:10:12,812
You lost?

1221
02:10:12,979 --> 02:10:15,481
I'm here to take you back
to Fort Kiowa...

1222
02:10:15,815 --> 02:10:17,984
...where you
will be tried for murder.

1223
02:10:18,318 --> 02:10:19,652
Is that so?

1224
02:10:19,902 --> 02:10:22,155
I ain't crazy
about your plan.

1225
02:10:22,655 --> 02:10:24,657
Besides, I got
one of my own.

1226
02:10:28,536 --> 02:10:29,912
(GUNSHOT)

1227
02:14:35,575 --> 02:14:36,617
(GASPS)

1228
02:14:38,452 --> 02:14:39,996
(HORSES WHINNYING)

1229
02:14:43,416 --> 02:14:44,417
(YELLS)

1230
02:14:49,297 --> 02:14:50,840
(PANTING)

1231
02:15:21,787 --> 02:15:23,789
(PANTING)

1232
02:16:17,802 --> 02:16:19,178
(RUSTLING)

1233
02:16:55,381 --> 02:16:56,799
(PANTING)

1234
02:17:06,517 --> 02:17:07,893
(YELPS)

1235
02:17:12,606 --> 02:17:13,941
(GRUNTING)

1236
02:17:29,957 --> 02:17:31,167
(GROANS)

1237
02:17:53,105 --> 02:17:55,858
We had a deal, Glass!

1238
02:17:58,944 --> 02:18:01,405
I tried to tell your boy,
all right?

1239
02:18:01,489 --> 02:18:04,450
I tried to tell him,
but he wouldn't listen

1240
02:18:04,533 --> 02:18:06,202
and he kept on screaming.

1241
02:18:06,285 --> 02:18:08,788
He was gonna get
everybody killed.

1242
02:18:10,456 --> 02:18:13,417
But you and me...
we had a deal.

1243
02:18:15,461 --> 02:18:17,713
You know what
happened out there.

1244
02:18:18,130 --> 02:18:21,175
And on my soul,
the Lord...He knows...

1245
02:18:21,258 --> 02:18:23,093
...what happened out there.

1246
02:18:25,805 --> 02:18:27,556
There was no deal.

1247
02:18:30,643 --> 02:18:32,353
You killed my boy.

1248
02:18:36,148 --> 02:18:38,234
Well, maybe you should've
raised a man,

1249
02:18:38,359 --> 02:18:40,069
instead of some
girlie little bitch.

1250
02:18:42,404 --> 02:18:43,739
(YELLING)

1251
02:18:47,243 --> 02:18:48,244
(GROANS)

1252
02:18:51,914 --> 02:18:53,749
Goddamn it.

1253
02:19:08,889 --> 02:19:10,182
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1254
02:19:22,444 --> 02:19:24,280
(CHOKING)

1255
02:19:27,950 --> 02:19:29,034
(GLASS SCREAMS)

1256
02:19:56,979 --> 02:19:58,397
(SCREAMING)

1257
02:20:17,833 --> 02:20:19,084
(GROANS)

1258
02:20:35,142 --> 02:20:36,518
(PANTING)

1259
02:20:38,354 --> 02:20:39,688
(SCREAMS)

1260
02:20:40,522 --> 02:20:41,774
(GROANS)

1261
02:20:45,194 --> 02:20:47,863
(GRUNTING)

1262
02:21:00,209 --> 02:21:01,669
(FITZGERALD HOWLS IN PAIN)

1263
02:21:16,976 --> 02:21:20,813
You came all this way
just for your revenge, huh?

1264
02:21:23,232 --> 02:21:25,567
Well, you enjoy it, Glass.

1265
02:21:26,402 --> 02:21:29,363
'Cause there ain't nothing
gonna bring your boy back.

1266
02:21:32,324 --> 02:21:33,993
No, it won't.

1267
02:21:38,831 --> 02:21:40,582
(HORSES APPROACHING)

1268
02:21:49,425 --> 02:21:50,843
(GLASS SPEAKING PAWNEE)

1269
02:21:55,556 --> 02:22:01,061
Revenge is in God's hands...

1270
02:22:01,061 --> 02:22:03,480
...not mine.

1271
02:22:27,546 --> 02:22:29,131
(FITZGERALD SCREAMING)

1272
02:22:30,966 --> 02:22:32,217
(EXHALES)

1273
02:22:36,805 --> 02:22:38,223
(FITZGERALD STOPS SCREAMING)

1274
02:24:52,733 --> 02:24:55,277
(GLASS'S WIFE
WHISPERING IN PAWNEE)

1275
02:26:20,153 --> 02:26:22,072
(GLASS EXHALING DEEPLY)
